Build a complete micro-SaaS web app called "ColdPing" using Next.js 16 and Tailwind CSS v4.

## CORE CONCEPT
A cold email personalization tool. The landing page IS the tool — no separate pages.
Users immediately see and can use the generator when they land on the site.
The Gemini API key must NEVER be exposed to the browser — all AI calls go through
a Next.js API route on the server side.

## TECH STACK
- Next.js 16 (App Router)
- Tailwind CSS v4
- No external database
- Gemini API called ONLY from a server-side API route (/api/generate)
- Gemini model: gemini-2.0-flash
- API key stored in .env.local as GEMINI_API_KEY (no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix)
- Email waitlist via Formspree (form ID stored in .env.local as FORMSPREE_ID)
- Frontend calls /api/generate — never calls Gemini directly

RULES:
- Max 150 words
- Open with ONE specific hook from their LinkedIn
- Mention one pain point specific to their role
- Never say "I hope this email finds you well"
- Never start with "My name is"
- Sound like a smart human, not a bot

